Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with star symbols.
Curator's comments: Worn pencil. Name Apollonios. Trimmed. Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 184,1). From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0004.34.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0759)
